The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are subfields of game theory and algorithmic game theory. The concept of core, which is central to the paper, is a well-known concept in cooperative game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing auctions, which falls under the subfield of mechanism design, and involves algorithms and data structures, which are covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves optimization and revenue maximization, which are covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
